    • Method Detail

      • peekNextToken

        com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonToken peekNextToken()
                                                   throws IOException,
                                                          com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonParseException
        Method that can be called when current token is not yet available via JsonParser.currentToken(), to try to figure out what kind of token will be eventually returned once the whole token is decoded, if known. Note that this may return JsonToken.NOT_AVAILABLE: this occurs either if current token is known (and thus no more parsing can be done yet), or if not enough content is available to even determine next token type (typically we only need a single byte, but in boundaries zero bytes is available).
        Returns:
        Token that will eventually be returned with a call to JsonParser.nextToken(), if known
        Throws:
        IOException
        com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonParseException
